  render_theorem(sec4, "Coupling-Ordered Freezing (S943, EMERGENT)", "D-channel freezes first (46%), then K (32%), then E/b/L (~0%). The coarsest structure locks down before the finer channels. Not designed. Not scheduled. The coupling hierarchy IS the natural crystallization order. Same ordering as diffusion noise schedule, confirmed across all architectures v0.1-v0.9.");
  render_p(sec4, "Results (v0.9 vs v0.8d dual bloom): 6790 majority crystallizations. Gibbs byte recovery: 94% (was 76%). Mirror score: 0.949 (was 0.945). Cross-consistency: 100%. L=11 near-parity at 74.1% (debug run, 50 epochs).");
  render_theorem(sec4, "Byte Unique Recovery (S618, PROVED)", "The ring denoises bytes WITHOUT a neural net. For any byte [0,255], corrupt one CRT channel, try all residues: EXACTLY ONE produces a valid byte. 100% recovery, 256/256, 5/5 channels. The neural net learns CONTENT, not correction. ECC is free.");
